## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="45d45-283">Web 部件控件集不实现任何默认行为<xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart.AuthorizationFilter%2A>属性。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="45d45-283">The Web Parts control set does not implement any default behavior for the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart.AuthorizationFilter%2A> property.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="45d45-284">但是，提供的属性，以便可以将任意字符串值分配给自定义<xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>控件，通过检查该属性可以<xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager>期间控制其<xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager.AuthorizeWebPart>事件以确定是否可以将控件添加到页面.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="45d45-284">However, the property is provided so that you can assign an arbitrary string value to a custom <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> control; this property can be checked by the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager> control during its <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager.AuthorizeWebPart> event to determine whether the control can be added to the page.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="45d45-285">在某些情况下，<xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart.AuthorizationFilter%2A>属性可能用于 ASP.NET 角色管理器功能，因此，如果用户位于某一特定角色中的字符串值<xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart.AuthorizationFilter%2A>属性满足某些条件设置由开发人员，则可以添加控件。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="45d45-285">In some cases, the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart.AuthorizationFilter%2A> property might be used with the ASP.NET role manager feature, so that if a user is in a certain role, and if the string value of the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart.AuthorizationFilter%2A> property meets certain conditions set by the developer, then the control can be added.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="45d45-286">此方法允许开发人员创建基于角色和它们指定了其他授权条件的组合的页的自定义视图。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="45d45-286">This approach allows developers to create custom views of a page based on a combination of roles and other authorization criteria that they specify.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="45d45-287">无法通过主题或样式表主题设置此属性。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="45d45-287">This property cannot be set by themes or style sheet themes.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="45d45-288">有关详细信息，请参阅<xref:System.Web.UI.ThemeableAttribute>并[ASP.NET 主题和外观](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/5df3ebbd-d46c-4502-9406-02f9df4ef2c3)。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="45d45-288">For more information, see <xref:System.Web.UI.ThemeableAttribute> and [ASP.NET Themes and Skins](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/5df3ebbd-d46c-4502-9406-02f9df4ef2c3).</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="45d45-289">此属性的个性化设置范围设置为<xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope.Shared>，并且只能由授权用户修改。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="45d45-289">The personalization scope of this property is set to <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope.Shared> and can be modified only by authorized users.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="45d45-290">有关详细信息，请参阅<xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizableAttribute>并[Web 部件个性化设置概述](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/7dc34f74-52aa-4082-b98d-2bcf9e07e320)。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="45d45-290">For more information, see <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizableAttribute> and [Web Parts Personalization Overview](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/7dc34f74-52aa-4082-b98d-2bcf9e07e320).</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="45d45-291">下面的代码示例演示如何将<xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart.AuthorizationFilter%2A>属性。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="45d45-291">The following code example demonstrates the use of the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart.AuthorizationFilter%2A> property.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="45d45-292">它演示了如何设置的自定义方法处理程序<xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager.AuthorizeWebPart>事件，以便该处理程序可以提供用于自定义筛选代码<xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager.OnAuthorizeWebPart%2A>方法。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="45d45-292">It shows how to set a custom method handler for the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager.AuthorizeWebPart> event, so that the handler can provide custom filtering code for the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager.OnAuthorizeWebPart%2A> method.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="45d45-293">此示例是页面开发人员提供筛选方案和授权的典型方式<xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>控件添加到页。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="45d45-293">This example would be a typical way for a page developer to provide a filtering scenario and authorization of <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> controls to be added to a page.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="45d45-294">在网页代码中，注意`<asp:webpartmanager>`元素具有`OnAuthorizeWebPart`具有分配给它的事件处理程序名称属性。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="45d45-294">In the Web page code, notice that the `<asp:webpartmanager>` element has the `OnAuthorizeWebPart` attribute with the name of the event handler assigned to it.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="45d45-295">此方法检查页上的控件是否具有其<xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart.AuthorizationFilter%2A>属性值设置为`admin`，以及如果是这样，则返回`true`，这意味着它们将被授权并添加到页面。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="45d45-295">This method checks whether the controls on the page have their <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart.AuthorizationFilter%2A> property value set to `admin`, and if so, returns `true`, which means that they will be authorized and added to the page.</span></span>  
  
> [!NOTE]
>  <span data-ttu-id="45d45-296">请注意，控件不具有分配给任何值<xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart.AuthorizationFilter%2A>属性还将添加，因为它们被假定不是筛选方案的一部分。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="45d45-296">Note that controls that do not have any value assigned to the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart.AuthorizationFilter%2A> property are added as well, because they are assumed not to be part of a filtering scenario.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="45d45-297">这将是筛选方案中的常见方法： 将筛选一些控件，并且其他人不会因为它们都假定为可供所有用户。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="45d45-297">This would be a common approach in a filtering scenario: some controls would be filtered, and others would not be, because they are presumed to be available for all users.</span></span>  
  
